        <div class="col-lg-8">
            <h3>Elon Musk</h3>
            <p>
                SpaceX was founded in 2002 by Elon Musk, an entrepreneur who is originally from South Africa and now holds citizenship in South Africa, Canada, and the United States.
                Elon Musk is also known for being a co-founder of Tesla Motors, an electric vehicle company, and should his first piece of software at the age of 12.
                Before starting SpaceX, Elon Musk had an original goal of starting life on Mars through the growth of plants.
                [<a href="https://www.cnbc.com/2019/03/20/spacex-rise-elon-musk-mars-dream.html">REF</a>]
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
    <h3>SpaceX's Vision</h3>
    <p>
        According to SpaceX’s website, they have an “ultimate goal of enabling people to love on other planets.”
        As a further description of this statement, SpaceX has also stated that they are “working on a next generation of fully reusable launch vehicles that will be the most powerful ever built, capable of carrying humans to Mars and other destinations in the Solar System”
        [<a href="https://www.cnbc.com/2019/03/20/spacex-rise-elon-musk-mars-dream.html">REF</a>].
        With humans on Mars, Elon Musk and SpaceX wish to create humanity to be a multi-planetary species.
    </p>
